g and development need of employees and teams in your region, translate that into an annual Learning and Development plan as well as ensure efficient and effective execution of that plan, with aim of equipping all employees with the required skills.      Desired Skills and ExperienceA strong relationship builder who can consults well with senior stakeholders. Ability to work in a multi-cultural, matrixed structure. Project Management skills. Customer focused. Business oriented. Significant work experience as a broad generalist with a strong balance of strategic and operational capability.About this companySancus AssociatesSancus Associates is a specialist, micro-niche agency, focusing solely on the Human Resources markets. Our consultants have unrivaled experience within their niche market areas, along with a unique understanding of the countries and cultures we operate in.Similar jobsSingaporePosted 10 hours agoSingaporePosted 4 days agoSingaporePosted 19 days agoSingaporePosted 22 days agoSingaporePosted 1 day agoSingaporePosted 22 days agoSingaporePosted 6 days agoSingaporePosted 19 days agoSingaporePosted 11 days agoSingaporePosted 27 days agoThis is a preview of the HR Business Partner APAC - Regional job at Sancus Associates. To view the full job listing, join LinkedIn - its free!Join LinkedIn - its free!People also searchedPeople also viewedSingaporePosted 21 days agoSingaporePosted 19 days agoSingaporePosted 22 days agoSingaporePosted 13 hours agoSingaporePosted 25 days agoSingaporePosted 19 days agoSingaporePosted 6 days agoSingaporePosted 19 days agoSingaporePosted 10 hours agoSingaporePosted 4 days ago
